"حِطَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for the purpose of asking thereby for the putting down of their heavy burdens from them, and they should be put down from them: (Ibn-Isráeel, TA:) the meaning is,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And say ye, Put Thou down from us our heavy burdens,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA,) or (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "our sins:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ibn-' Arafeh, K:) or ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and say ye,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Our petition is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HiT~apN", "text_ar": "حِطَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that Thou wouldest put down from us our sins:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Aboo-Is- hák, K:) or, accord. to some,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HiT~ap", "text_ar": "حِطَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a word which the children of Israel were commanded to say; and if they said it, their heavy burdens, or sins, were put down: (S, TA:) accord. to IAar, it is the saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA A_il`ha A_il~aA A@ll~`hu", "text_ar": "لَا اـِلٰهَ اـِلَّا ا@للّٰهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) or it means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "forgiveness:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(I' Ab:) or our affair is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an alighting and abiding"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in this town: (Bd in ii. 55:) and there is another reading,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wa quwluwA HiT~apF", "text_ar": "وَ قُولُوا حِطَّةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is explained in two ways; either by making the verb to govern the noun, as though he had said,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and say ye a saying which shall put down from you your heavy burdens,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sins;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or by making the noun to be in the accus. case as an inf. n. meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "supplicating"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "petitioning"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that God may put down from you your heavy burdens,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sins"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AuHoTuTi A@ll~ahum~a A^awozaAranaA HiT~apF", "text_ar": "اُحْطُطِ ا@للَّهُمَّ اَوْزَارَنَا حِطَّةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) but they changed this saying, (Fr, Sgh, K,) using for it a Nabathean expression; (Fr, TA;) saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hiT~iY sumohaAvFA", "text_ar": "هِطِّى سُمْهَاثًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e. ” red wheat, “ (Sgh, K,) accord. to Es-Suddee and Mujáhid; or, accord. to IAar,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HinoTapF $umoqaAyaA", "text_ar": "حِنْطَةً شُمْقَايَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e. ” good wheat. “ (Sgh, TA.) You say also, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saA^alahu AlHiT~iyTaY", "text_ar": "سَاَلَهُ الحِطِّيطَى", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHiT~apa", "text_ar": "الحِطَّةَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He asked of him the putting down of his heavy burden from him:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his sin"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) And it is said in a trad., that when God tries a person with a trial in his body,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa lahu HiT~apN", "text_ar": "هُوَ لَهُ حِطَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It is to him a mode of putting down from him his sins."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHiT~apu", "text_ar": "الحِطَّةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A name of the month of Ramadán,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the Gospel, or some other book: (Az, K, * TA:) because it puts down somewhat of the sin of him who observes the fast thereof. (Az, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A decrease,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "state of diminution, in respect of rank,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "station:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) [or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "low,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lowest, rank,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "station:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for] ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHuTuTu", "text_ar": "الحُطُطُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, TA,) which is its pl., (TA,) is explained as signifying, (K, TA,) on the authority of IAar, (TA,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maraAkibu", "text_ar": "مَرَاكِبُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~ifali", "text_ar": "السِّفَلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or correctly"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maraAtibu Als~ifali", "text_ar": "مَرَاتِبُ السِّفَلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K, TA:) the latter [meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the ranks,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "stations, of the lowest,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "meanest, of mankind,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is the right reading, as verified by Az. (TA.)"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 593}], "source_refs": ["S", "TA", "Fr", "Sgh", "K"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}